Configuration Steps
Step 1: Update API Base URL
Edit src/services/api.js:

// Replace this:
const API_BASE_URL = 'https://your-api-endpoint.com/api';

// With your actual API URL:
const API_BASE_URL = 'https://api.yourdomain.com/api';
Step 2: Remove Mock Data
In src/services/api.js, uncomment the real API calls and remove mock data:

// Remove MOCK_PRODUCTS array

// In getProducts function:
getProducts: async () => {
  try {
    const response = await axios.get(`${API_BASE_URL}/products`);
    return response.data;
  } catch (error) {
    console.error('Error fetching products:', error);
    throw error;
  }
},
Step 3: Test API Integration
Start the app
Check console for errors
Test each feature:
View products
Place order
Track order
Data Types Reference
Game Type Enum
1 = BGMI
2 = FreeFire
Payment Status Enum
1 = Pending
2 = Completed
Order Status Enum
1 = Pending
2 = Processing
3 = Fulfilled
Authentication (Optional)
If your API requires authentication:

import axios from 'axios';

const api = axios.create({
  baseURL: API_BASE_URL,
  headers: {
    'Authorization': 'Bearer YOUR_API_KEY',
    'Content-Type': 'application/json'
  }
});
Error Handling
The app includes basic error handling. Customize error messages in each API function.

Testing
Use tools like Postman to test your API endpoints before integrating.

